        "heading_NDEHEJ": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "text": "International Warranty Policy",
            "marker_style": "style1",
            "size": "h4",
            "marker_color": "#fd6262"
          }
        },
        "text_9khC3E": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>We stand behind everything we make. If, during the 2-year warranty period of your anymaka product, it stops working or has any defects, we will do our best to replace any defective part free of charge with proof of purchase. We will provide replacement parts or repair tools and instructions, but the customer will be responsible for installation. If your product is not repairable, we will replace a product covered by this limited warranty.</p><p>This warranty applies only to customers who purchase directly from the anymaka website, stores, or an authorized dealer and does not cover second-hand purchases. If you purchased from an authorized dealer, please provide proof of purchase with any warranty claims.</p>",
            "size": "text-size-regular"
          }
        },
        "heading_KjdMkU": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Manufacturing Defects",
            "marker_style": "style1",
            "size": "h4",
            "marker_color": "#fd6262"
          }
        },
        "text_mtKVKr": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><strong>PLEASE NOTE</strong>: This warranty specifically covers issues that result from manufacturing defects. We take responsibility for any defective materials (such as zippers, buckles, fabrics, etc.) or workmanship (including seams and construction) under the anymaka Limited Warranty. However, when it comes to applying our warranty, anymaka reserves the right to use discretion.</p><p>The following situations are not covered by this warranty:</p><ul><li><strong>Normal wear-and-tear</strong>, including damage that naturally occurs due to regular use and agingof the product.</li><li><strong>Cosmetic wear</strong> unrelated to function or safety, such as loose threads, scuffs, or stains.</li><li><strong>Misuse </strong>such as jumping, swinging, or exceeding weight limits.</li><li><strong>UV Damage</strong> from exposure to elements.</li><li><strong>Accidents</strong> that are not caused by the integrity of the product, such as rips and tears caused by animals or sharp objects or burns from fire embers or cigarettes. </li><li><strong>Altering</strong> the product to change the functionality, or not used for its intended purpose. </li><li>Cord or stuff sack replacement.</li><li>Lost or stolen gear.</li></ul>",
            "size": "text-size-regular"
          }
        },
        "heading_73jp8h": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Disclaimer of Liability",
            "marker_style": "style1",
            "size": "h4",
            "marker_color": "#fd6262"
          }
        },
        "text_9Jx6fj": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Stay safe. Before using our products, make sure to read and follow all safety instructions carefully. Although our gear is designed with top-notch quality and safety in mind, anymaka is not liable for injury to yourself or others as a result of using our products. We urge you to diligently read and adhere to the safety instructions and use gear wisely and with safety in mind.</p><p>If you have any questions, feel free to contact us at <a href=\"mailto:hi@anymaka.com\" title=\"mailto:hi@anymaka.com\">hi@anymaka.com</a>.</p>",
            "size": "text-size-regular"
          }
        }
      },
